---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import FAQSchema from "../../../components/FAQSchema.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Leather Sofa Cleaning & Conditioning | Montreal & Laval"
  description="Expert in-home leather furniture cleaning, conditioning and protection. Stain removal, sebum elimination, and skin revitalization with premium creams. Free estimate."
>
  <section class="split-hero-container">
    <div class="container full-width-split">
      <div class="split-layout">
        <!-- LEFT COLUMN: TEXT -->
        <div class="split-content fade-in-section">
          <span class="service-cat-badge">LEATHER SOFA</span>
          <h1 class="split-title text-gradient-empire">
            Leather Cleaning, Conditioning and Protection
          </h1>

          <div class="problem-statement fade-in-up delay-100">
            <h3 class="problem-title">The Problem:</h3>
            <p class="problem-text">
              Leather is a porous natural material. Without professional cleaning and nourishment, 
              the sun, heating, and body sebum dry it out, crack it, and permanently alter its 
              color in irreversible ways.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="lead-text fade-in-up delay-200">
            Protect your investment. Our <strong>expert leather treatment</strong> deep-cleans 
            the pores, eliminates stains (pen, denim transfer), and rehydrates the skin with 
            premium revitalizing creams to restore its original suppleness and shine.
          </p>

          <div class="cta-group fade-in-up delay-300">
            <a href="tel:5148939939" class="btn btn-primary pulse-btn">
              <span class="icon">📞</span> (514) 893-9939
            </a>
            <button
              onclick="window.openEstimationWidget()"
              class="btn btn-outline-reveal"
            >
              <span class="icon">⚡</span> Instant Estimate
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT COLUMN: SLIDESHOW/IMAGE -->
        <div class="split-image-wrapper fade-in-section delay-200">
          <div class="slideshow-container">
            <img
              src="/images/catalog/photo-leather-final.webp"
              alt="Technician conditioning a leather sofa - Empire Cleaning Group"
              class="slide active"
              width="1200"
              height="800"
              fetchpriority="high"
              loading="eager"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="image-gradient-overlay"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MAIN SECTIONS -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 5rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-layout">
        <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
        <div class="service-main">
          
          <div class="fade-in-section delay-100" style="margin-top: 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title text-gradient-empire">
              Our Expert Process (On-Site)
            </h2>
            <div class="process-timeline" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
              <div class="process-step">
                <div class="step-marker">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                  <h3>Inspection and Identification</h3>
                  <p>Determining the type of leather (pigmented, aniline, semi-aniline, nubuck) to choose the pH of the most appropriate cleaning product without risking damage.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="process-step">
                <div class="step-marker">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                  <h3>Deep Cleaning (Pore Extraction)</h3>
                  <p>Application of a gentle cleanser using special brushes to open the leather pores and extract embedded dirt, perspiration and body oils.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="process-step">
                <div class="step-marker">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                  <h3>Specific Stain Treatment</h3>
                  <p>Manual treatment of problematic stains such as dye transfer (blue jeans on white leather), pen ink stains or grease halos.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="process-step">
                <div class="step-marker">4</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                  <h3>Conditioning and Nourishment (Revitalization)</h3>
                  <p>A crucial step. We manually massage the leather with a rich revitalizing cream. It penetrates the skin to restore suppleness and prevent future cracking.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="process-step">
                <div class="step-marker">5</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                  <h3>Protection (Sealant / Polishing)</h3>
                  <p>Application of an invisible barrier that acts as a shield against future liquid spills, dirt, and UV rays from the sun (which discolor leather).</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-box fade-in-section delay-100">
              <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 10px;">
                Why does your leather furniture age poorly?
              </h3>
              <p>
                Leather is exactly like human skin. If it isn't washed and moisturized, it peels and cracks. The most common mistake is using household cleaning products or "miracle wipes" from big-box stores. 
                These products contain strong detergents or synthetic waxes that dry leather over time and destroy its original protective finish. By calling our experts, you guarantee a pH-balanced treatment 
                that extends the life of your living room furniture by several years.
              </p>
            </div>

          <!-- BENEFITS SECTION -->
          <div class="fade-in-section delay-200" style="margin-top: 4rem;">
            <h2 class="section-title text-gradient-empire">
              Why have your leather cleaned by professionals?
            </h2>
            <div class="benefits-grid">
              <div class="benefit-item">
                <div class="check-circle">✓</div>
                <span><strong>Crack prevention:</strong> Rehydrates the natural oils in the skin to prevent permanent drying caused by sun and heating systems.</span>
              </div>
              <div class="benefit-item">
                <div class="check-circle">✓</div>
                <span><strong>Sebum elimination:</strong> Dissolves accumulation rings of grease and perspiration on armrests and headrests.</span>
              </div>
              <div class="benefit-item">
                <div class="check-circle">✓</div>
                <span><strong>Silky finish with no sticky residue:</strong> Unlike supermarket waxes, our products don't leave the furniture looking artificially shiny or slippery.</span>
              </div>
              <div class="benefit-item">
                <div class="check-circle">✓</div>
                <span><strong>Embedded odor removal:</strong> Eliminates the impregnation of sweat or smoke that can seep into leather over time.</span>
              </div>
              <div class="benefit-item">
                <div class="check-circle">✓</div>
                <span><strong>Carbon Conditioning and Protection:</strong> After cleaning, we apply a rich professional conditioning cream to prevent future cracking. We also offer the application of <a href="/en/services/protecteur" style="color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">a premium stain protector (Carbon Protector)</a> that blocks the absorption of pen ink, food oil, or fabric dye.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          </div>

          <!-- SERVICE ZONES -->
          <div class="zones-section" style="margin-top: 4rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.4rem;">Service Areas — Leather Furniture Cleaning</h3>
            <p>We travel throughout Greater Montreal to treat your leather at home.</p>

            <div class="city-group">
              <p class="city-lead">🏙️ Montreal (East and West)</p>
              <div class="badges-container">
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Montreal</span>
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Westmount</span>
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Mont-Royal</span>
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Outremont</span>
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 LaSalle</span>
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 RDP / PAT</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="city-group">
              <p class="city-lead">🏘️ Laval</p>
              <div class="badges-container">
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Laval (all sectors)</span>
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Chomedey</span>
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Sainte-Rose</span>
                <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Vimont</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="city-group">
              <p class="city-lead">🌿 South Shore of Montreal</p>
              <div class="badges-container">
                <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Longueuil</span>
                <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Brossard</span>
                <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Saint-Lambert</span>
                <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Saint-Hubert</span>
                <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Greenfield Park</span>
                <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Boucherville</span>
                <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Saint-Bruno</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ -->
          <div class="fade-in-section delay-300" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
            <h2 class="section-title text-gradient-empire">
              Frequently Asked Questions — Leather Service
            </h2>
            <FAQSchema
              faqs={[
                {
                  question: "Can you remove blue jean dye transfer from my white leather sofa?",
                  answer: "It depends on how long the transfer has been there and the type of leather. Pigmented leather can often be cleaned of this transfer if treated quickly. However, if the clothing dye has had time to migrate deeply into the leather's varnish (often due to body heat), it may act as a permanent dye. In the majority of cases, we obtain excellent results or a very noticeable fading.",
                },
                {
                  question: "Do you repair torn, peeling, or cat-scratched leather?",
                  answer: "Our expertise is strictly in deep cleaning, conditioning and protecting leather health. We do not perform repairs of tears, re-dyeing (coloring) or panel replacement (upholstery). If your leather is peeling because it is 'bonded leather' (fake leather), unfortunately cleaning cannot save the material that is disintegrating.",
                },
                {
                  question: "How often should I have my leather furniture treated?",
                  answer: "For leather maintained in perfect condition, a professional treatment (cleaning and conditioning cream application) every 12 to 18 months is ideal. If your furniture is directly exposed to sunlight or near a heat source (fireplace, electric baseboards), the leather will dry out faster; annual treatment is then strongly recommended.",
                },
                {
                  question: "Can I use supermarket cleaning wipes?",
                  answer: "This is strongly discouraged by all quality upholstery leather manufacturers. Most wipes contain solvents, alcohol or silicones that dry leather and destroy its protective varnish (Top Coat). On the surface, your sofa looks clean and shiny, but long-term, you are accelerating its aging and promoting cracking.",
                },
                {
                  question: "How long does the conditioner take to dry before sitting on the furniture?",
                  answer: "Generally, you can resume using your leather furniture about 1 to 2 hours after we leave. This delay allows the conditioning cream to fully penetrate the leather pores and the protective sealant to dry evenly to avoid staining your clothing.",
                },
                {
                  question: "Do you clean all types of leather, including suede or nubuck?",
                  answer: "Finished (pigmented) leather represents 90% of the furniture we treat and this process is very effective. For unfinished, semi-aniline, or very porous leathers like nubuck, the process is different and more delicate, as these leathers absorb liquids instantly. Our technicians will inspect your furniture before starting and recommend the dry or specific method adapted to your sensitive leather type.",
                },
              ]}
            />
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- SIDEBAR -->
        <aside class="service-sidebar">
          <div class="sticky-card fade-in-section">
            <h3 class="card-title text-gradient-gold">
              Instant Estimate
            </h3>
            <p class="card-desc">Call us for an immediate response.</p>

            <a
              href="tel:5148939939"
              class="btn btn-gradient-green full-width pop-effect pulse-phone"
            >
              <span class="icon">📞</span> (514) 893-9939
            </a>

            <p class="text-center" style="margin: 1rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #888;">
              or
            </p>

            <button
              onclick="window.openEstimationWidget()"
              class="btn btn-gradient-green full-width"
            >
              Online Estimate
            </button>

            <div class="guarantee-badge">
              <span>🛡️ Nourished & Protected Leather</span>
              <div style="margin-top: 5px; color: #ffbf00; font-weight: bold;">
                ★★★★★
              </div>
              <span style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: #666;">5-Star Service</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<script is:inline>
  (function () {
    const slides = document.querySelectorAll(".slide");
    if (slides.length > 0) {
      let currentSlide = 0;
      const intervalTime = 4000;
      setInterval(() => {
        slides[currentSlide].classList.remove("active");
        currentSlide = (currentSlide + 1) % slides.length;
        slides[currentSlide].classList.add("active");
      }, intervalTime);
    }
  })();
</script>

<style>
  /* HERO SPLIT LAYOUT */
  .split-hero-container {
    background-color: #fff;
    padding-top: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    width: 100vw;
  }
  .full-width-split { width: 100%; max-width: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .split-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    align-items: stretch;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }
  .split-content {
    background-color: #ffffff;
    padding: 100px 4rem 4rem 10%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .service-cat-badge {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .split-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 3.5vw, 4rem);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .problem-statement {
    background: #ffffff;
    border-left: 4px solid #ff4444;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(174, 206, 235, 0.3);
  }
  .problem-title { font-size: 1rem; color: #cc0000; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 700; }
  .problem-text { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--color-text-main); font-style: italic; }
  .lead-text { font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-main); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; max-width: 650px; }
  .cta-group { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .split-image-wrapper { position: relative; height: 100%; min-height: 500px; width: 100%; border-radius: 0; transform: none; box-shadow: none; margin: 0; background-color: #fff; }
  .slideshow-container { position: relative; width: 100%; height: 100%; overflow: hidden; }
  .slide { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 1.5s ease-in-out; }
  .slide.active { opacity: 1; }

  /* LAYOUT */
  .service-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.8fr 1fr; gap: 5rem; }
  .section-title { font-size: 1.8rem; color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 2px solid #eee; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; display: inline-block; }

  /* PROCESS TIMELINE */
  .process-timeline { position: relative; padding-left: 20px; }
  .process-timeline::before { content: ''; position: absolute; top: 0; bottom: 0; left: 20px; width: 2px; background: #e0e0e0; }
  .process-step { position: relative; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-left: 50px; }
  .process-step:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .step-marker { position: absolute; left: -16px; top: 0; width: 34px; height: 34px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-primary); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: bold; border: 4px solid white; box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }
  .step-content h3 { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .step-content p { color: #555; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  .info-box { background-color: #f8f9fa; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; border-radius: 4px; }

  .btn-outline-reveal {
    background: transparent; border: 2px solid var(--color-primary); color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; cursor: pointer;
    border-radius: 4px; transition: all 0.3s ease; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .btn-outline-reveal:hover { background: var(--color-primary); color: white; transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }

  /* BENEFITS */
  .benefits-grid { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .benefit-item { display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start; }
  .check-circle { width: 28px; height: 28px; min-width: 28px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-primary); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: bold; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 2px; }

  /* ZONES */
  .city-group { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .city-lead { font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .badges-container { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .badge { padding: 0.4rem 0.9rem; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid transparent; }
  .badge-blue { background: #e8f4fd; border-color: #c5dff0; }
  .badge-green { background: #f0faf0; border-color: #b8ddb8; }

  /* SIDEBAR */
  .service-sidebar { position: relative; }
  .sticky-card { background: white; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); position: sticky; top: 2rem; border: 1px solid #eee; }
  .card-title { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 800; }
  .card-desc { color: #666; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .full-width { width: 100%; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; justify-content: center; }
  .guarantee-badge { margin-top: 2rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px dashed #eee; text-align: center; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 600; }

  /* RESPONSIVE */
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .split-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; min-height: auto; }
    .split-content { padding: 3rem 1.5rem; order: 1; }
    .split-image-wrapper { order: 2; height: 400px; min-height: 0; }
    .lead-text { max-width: 100%; }
    .cta-group { display: none !important; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .service-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
